{"error":false,"analysis":"The experiment successfully analyzed the relationship between the composite ASVAB score and socioeconomic status (SES) using the available dataset. The correlation coefficient between the composite ASVAB score and SES is 0.46, indicating a moderate positive correlation. This suggests that higher academic ability, as measured by the ASVAB, is associated with higher SES.

